  38. ‌  let mask =
  39.     let open Nativeint in
  40.     sub (shift_left one 8) one

  42.   let pat_as_string p =
  43.     let rec digits k n p =
  44.       if n <= 0 then k
  45.       else
  46.         let d = Nativeint.to_int (Nativeint.logand mask p) in
  47.         let d = Char.escaped (Char.chr d) in
  48.         digits (d::k) (n-1) (Nativeint.shift_right_logical p  8) in
  49.     let ds = digits [] Arch.size_addr p in
  50.     let ds =
  51.       if Arch.big_endian then ds else List.rev ds in
  52.     String.concat "" ds

  54. ‌  let do_pp_cases chan cases =
  55.     List.iter
  56.       (fun (ps,_) ->
  57.         Printf.fprintf chan "  [%s]\n"
  58.           (String.concat "; " (List.map pat_as_string ps)))
  59.       cases

  61.   let pp_cases chan tag cases =
  62.     Printf.eprintf "%s:\n" tag ;
  63.     do_pp_cases chan cases

  65.   let pp_match chan tag idxs cases =
  66.     Printf.eprintf
  67.       "%s: idx=[%s]\n" tag
  68.       (String.concat "; " (List.map Int.to_string idxs)) ;
  69.     do_pp_cases chan cases

  76.   let mk_let_cell id str ind body =

  84.     Clet(id, cell, body)

  94.     in
  95.     Cifthenelse (test, dbg, ifso, dbg, ifnot, dbg)

  120. ‌  let pat_of_string str =
  121.     let len = String.length str in
  122.     let n = len / Arch.size_addr + 1 in
  123.     let get_byte i =
  124.       if i < len then int_of_char str.[i]
  125.       else if i < n * Arch.size_addr - 1 then 0
  126.       else n * Arch.size_addr - 1 - len in
  127. ‌    let mk_word ind =
  128.       let w = ref 0n in
  129.       let imin = ind * Arch.size_addr
  130.       and imax = (ind + 1) * Arch.size_addr - 1 in
  131.       if Arch.big_endian then
  132.         for i = imin to imax do
  133.           w := Nativeint.logor (Nativeint.shift_left !w 8)
  134.               (Nativeint.of_int (get_byte i));
  135.         done
  136.       else
  137.         for i = imax downto imin do
  138.           w := Nativeint.logor (Nativeint.shift_left !w 8)
  139.               (Nativeint.of_int (get_byte i));
  140.         done;
  141.       !w in
  142. ‌    let rec mk_words ind  =
  143.       if ind >= n then []
  144.       else mk_word ind::mk_words (ind+1) in
  145.     mk_words 0

  151.   module IntSet = Set.Make(IntArg)
  152.   module NativeSet = Set.Make(Nativeint)

  154. ‌  let rec add_one sets ps = match sets,ps with
  155.   | [],[] -> []
  156.   | set::sets,p::ps ->
  157.       let sets = add_one sets ps in
  158.       NativeSet.add p set::sets
  159.   | _,_ -> assert false

  161. ‌  let count_arities cases = match cases with
  162.   | [] -> assert false
  163.   | (ps,_)::_ ->
  164.       let sets =
  165.         List.fold_left
  166.           (fun sets (ps,_) -> add_one sets ps)
  167.           (List.map (fun _ -> NativeSet.empty) ps) cases in
  168.       List.map NativeSet.cardinal sets

  170. ‌  let count_arities_first cases =
  171.     let set =
  172.       List.fold_left
  173.         (fun set case -> match case with
  174.         | (p::_,_) -> NativeSet.add p set
  175.         | _ -> assert false)
  176.         NativeSet.empty cases in
  177.     NativeSet.cardinal set

  179. ‌  let count_arities_length cases =
  180.     let set =
  181.       List.fold_left
  182.         (fun set (ps,_) -> IntSet.add (List.length ps) set)
  183.         IntSet.empty cases in
  184.     IntSet.cardinal set

  186. ‌  let best_col =
  187.     let rec do_rec kbest best k = function
  188.       | [] -> kbest
  189.       | x::xs ->
  190.           if x < best then
  191.             do_rec k x (k+1) xs
  192.           else
  193.             do_rec kbest best (k+1) xs in
  194.     let smallest = do_rec (-1) max_int 0 in
  195.     fun cases ->
  196.       let ars = count_arities cases in
  197.       smallest ars

  199. ‌  let swap_list =
  200.     let rec do_rec k xs = match xs with
  201.     | [] -> assert false
  202.     | x::xs ->
  203.         if k <= 0 then [],x,xs
  204.         else
  205.           let xs,mid,ys = do_rec (k-1) xs in
  206.           x::xs,mid,ys in
  207.     fun k xs ->
  208.       let xs,x,ys = do_rec  k xs in
  209.       x::xs @ ys

  211. ‌  let swap k idxs cases =
  212.     if k = 0 then idxs,cases
  213.     else
  214.       let idxs = swap_list k idxs
  215.       and cases =
  216.         List.map
  217.           (fun (ps,act) -> swap_list k ps,act)
  218.           cases in
  219.       if dbg then begin
  220.         pp_match stderr "SWAP" idxs cases
  221.       end ;
  222.       idxs,cases

  224. ‌  let best_first idxs cases = match idxs with
  225.   | []|[_] -> idxs,cases (* optimisation: one column only *)
  226.   | _ ->
  227.       let k = best_col cases in
  228.       swap k idxs cases

  234.   module Divide(O:Set.OrderedType) = struct

  236.     module OMap = Map.Make(O)

  238. ‌    let divide cases =
  239.       let env =
  240.         List.fold_left
  241.           (fun env (p,psact) ->
  242.             let old =
  243.               try OMap.find p env
  244.               with Not_found -> [] in
  245.             OMap.add p ((psact)::old) env)
  246.           OMap.empty cases in
  247.       let r =  OMap.fold (fun key v k -> (key,v)::k) env [] in
  248.       List.rev r (* Now sorted *)
  249.   end

  257.     module DivideNative = Divide(Nativeint)

  259. ‌    let by_cell cases =
  260.       DivideNative.divide
  261.         (List.map
  262.            (fun case -> match case with
  263.            | (p::ps),act -> p,(ps,act)
  264.            | [],_ -> assert false)
  265.            cases)

  267. (* Split into two halves *)

  269.     let rec do_split idx env = match env with
  270.     | [] -> assert false
  271.     | (midkey,_ as x)::rem ->
  272.         if idx <= 0 then [],midkey,env
  273.         else
  274.           let lt,midkey,ge = do_split (idx-1) rem in
  275.           x::lt,midkey,ge

  277. ‌    let split_env len env = do_split (len/2) env

  279. (* Switch according to one cell *)

  281. (*
  282.   Emit the switch, here as a comparison tree.
  283.   Argument compile_rec is to be called to compile the rest of patterns,
  284.   as match_on_cell can be called in two different contexts :
  285.   from do_compile_pats and top_compile below.
  286. *)
  287. ‌    let match_oncell compile_rec str default idx env =
  288.       let id = gen_cell_id () in
  289.       let rec comp_rec env =
  290.         let len = List.length env in
  291.         if len <= 3 then
  292.           List.fold_right
  293.             (fun (key,cases) ifnot ->
  294.               mk_eq id key
  295.                 (compile_rec str default cases)
  296.               ifnot)
  297.             env default
  298.         else
  299.           let lt,midkey,ge = split_env len env in
  300.           mk_lt id midkey (comp_rec lt) (comp_rec ge) in
  301.       mk_let_cell (VP.create id) str idx (comp_rec env)

  303. (*
  304.   Recursive 'list of cells' compile function:
  305.   - choose the matched cell and switch on it
  306.   - notice: patterns (and idx) all have the same length
  307. *)

  309. ‌    let rec do_compile_pats idxs str default cases =
  310.       if dbg then begin
  311.         pp_match stderr "COMPILE" idxs cases
  312.       end ;
  313.       match idxs with
  314.       | [] ->
  315.           begin match cases with
  316.           | [] -> default
  317.           | (_,e)::_ -> e
  318.           end
  319.       | _::_ ->
  320.           let idxs,cases = best_first idxs cases in
  321.           begin match idxs with
  322.           | [] -> assert false
  323.           | idx::idxs ->
  324.               match_oncell
  325.                 (do_compile_pats idxs) str default idx (by_cell cases)
  326.           end


  329. (* Group by size *)

  331.     module DivideInt = Divide(IntArg)


  334. ‌    let by_size cases =
  335.       DivideInt.divide
  336.         (List.map
  337.            (fun (ps,_ as case) -> List.length ps,case)
  338.            cases)
  339. (*
  340.   Switch according to pattern size
  341.   Argument from_ind is the starting index, it can be zero
  342.   or one (when the switch on the cell 0 has already been performed.
  343.   In that latter case pattern len is string length-1 and is corrected.
  344. *)

  346.     let compile_by_size dbg from_ind str default cases =
  347.       let size_cases =
  348.         List.map
  349.           (fun (len,cases) ->
  350.             let len = len+from_ind in
  351.             let act =
  352.               do_compile_pats
  353.                 (interval from_ind len)
  354.                 str default  cases in
  355.             (len,act))
  356.           (by_size cases) in
  357. ‌      let id = gen_size_id () in
  358. ‌      let switch = I.transl_switch dbg (Cvar id) 1 max_int size_cases default in
  359.       mk_let_size (VP.create id) str switch

  361. (*
  362.   Compilation entry point: we choose to switch
  363.   either on size or on first cell, using the
  364.   'least discriminant' heuristics.
  365. *)
  366. ‌    let top_compile debuginfo str default cases =
  367.       let a_len = count_arities_length cases
  368.       and a_fst = count_arities_first cases in
  369.       if a_len <= a_fst then begin
  370.         if dbg then pp_cases stderr "SIZE" cases ;
  371.         compile_by_size debuginfo 0 str default cases
  372.       end else begin
  373.         if dbg then pp_cases stderr "FIRST COL" cases ;
  374. ‌        let compile_size_rest str default cases =
  375.           compile_by_size debuginfo 1 str default cases in
  376.         match_oncell compile_size_rest str default 0 (by_cell cases)
  377.       end

  379. (* Module entry point *)

  381. ‌    let catch dbg arg k = match arg with
  382.     | Cexit (_e,[]) ->  k arg
  383.     | _ ->
  384.         let e =  next_raise_count () in
  385.         ccatch (e,[],k (Cexit (e,[])),arg,dbg)

  387. ‌    let compile dbg str default cases =
  388. (* We do not attempt to really optimise default=None *)
  389.       let cases,default = match cases,default with
  390.       | (_,e)::cases,None
  391.       | cases,Some e -> cases,e
  392.       | [],None -> assert false in
  393.       let cases =
  394.         List.rev_map
  395.           (fun (s,act) -> pat_of_string s,act)
  396.           cases in
  397.       catch dbg default (fun default -> top_compile dbg str default cases)

  399.   end
